b'@scottgordonwi I see it now. My apologies. But I still think he cherry picked a couple sillier bits and framed them in a way to make me look as empty and stupid as possible. The arc of that special was about my dad dying, which I think does hit "deeper", but that doesn\'t support his argument.'

b'@riverguardian @scottgordonwi "Vapid", "bland", and suggesting that I\'m too much a fanboy to form a real opnion. Also he cherry picked bits to ridicule them to make his point, but left out the entire arc of the special being about that "deeper" thing he claims I lack.'

b"@scottgordonwi I'm not asking for anyone to kiss my ass. Just asking for fairness. And if you or your writers want to go at someone that hard & mean--fine--but you should demand they have enough current experience w/ the thing they're going after to have an informed opinion. That's all!"
b'@scottgordonwi PS - I invite you as well, Scott!'

b"@scottgordonwi This is why I invited David to be my guest at a show. A responsbile journalist would take that challenge. If he hates it after that, then by all means dump on me. And if I'm wrong about his never seeing me live or anytime recently, I will happily publicly apologize."

b'@scottgordonwi But we evolve as performers. My last special was all about the death of my father, which you\'d be hard pressed to call "bland". So that\'s why it reads fishy to me. Too many personal attacks and not anything about what it\'s like to see me live.'

b"@scottgordonwi If you want to be in the ragebait buisness, that's fine, but you should also be prepared to be called out for it. See, other people get to form opnions about your opinions. Look, I'll be honest, I can't watch my first special. It makes my skin crawl. But it's almost a decade old."
